-- Italian Stocks: Lottomatica, Prelios, UniCredit are Active
-- B y   A d r i a   C i m i n o
-- 2011-02-08T17:06:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-08/italian-stocks-lottomatica-prelios-unicredit-are-active.html
  Italy ’s benchmark  FTSE MIB Index 
slipped 0.3 percent to 22,734.17 at the 5:30 p.m. close in
Milan.  The following stocks were among the most active in the
Italian market today.    Lottomatica SpA  (LTO IM) advanced 3.4 percent to 10.83
euros. CA Cheuvreux raised its recommendation on the manager of
Italy’s Lotto game to “outperform” from “underperform.”    Prelios SpA  (PRS IM) gained 5 percent to 59 euro cents.
Cheuvreux raised its recommendation on the stock to
“outperform” from “underperform.”    UniCredit SpA  (UCG IM) lost 1.8 percent to 1.87 euros. The
bank’s Italian business posted a net loss of 50 million euros
($68 million) in 2010,  Il Sole 24 Ore  reported, citing a
presentation to bank executives by general manager  Roberto
Nicastro .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Adria Cimino in Paris at 
 acimino1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:  David Merritt  at   dmerritt1@bloomberg.net . 